product.description: Designed using heavy gauge steel core, this set of two Calphalon baking pans ensures evenly heated and perfectly browned cookies, cakes, and more. Its interior has interlocking nonstick layers, offering up to 2X better release than Calphalon Classic Bakeware, leading to long-lasting, high-performance usage. Raised edges on this baking sheet facilitate a no-spill baking experience, making it versatile for everything from cookies to sheet cakes. Finish your baking session with an easy cleanup, thanks to its dishwasher-safe properties and excellent reliability backed by Calphalon's full lifetime warranty.

top_reviews.title: Phenomenal baking sheets!
top_reviews.body: This pair of Calphalon Baking Sheets are nothing short of phenomenal!!  I purchased these because I inadvertently ruined a different brands pair of sheets we had for many years because I am a moron. LOL I cooked something on it and some substance baked into and stained the sheet. Because I am an absolute genius, I used an SOS/Brillo type of pad on a non-stick item when other, less harsh methods weren't working to clean it. You get the picture.  These are great and my wife won't let me clean them. I totally understand why.  She has baked a variety of items on these sheets and she barely needs a spatula to remove what she has cooked. She could remove the items by hand if they weren't so hot. They are wonderful sheets with easy removal of what you are going to bake or cook on them. They clean easily and look great. They are very durable and a perfect size for whatever you are going to use them for.  While these are more expensive than other brands and sheets these are 100% worth the money. I definitely recommend purchasing these as you won't be disappointed. Unless you clean them with an SOS or Brillo type of pad. If you do, please know I can make room in my doghouse for you. Read more

date.raw: Reviewed in the United States on November 7, 2023

top_reviews.title: Frugal, Scratch-cooking, Mama review
top_reviews.body: I'll first say I gave it five stars for the three months of durability it has endured. A LOT. These two pans quickly became my two favorite pans. I know some of you can relate to the anxiety of having to replace a beloved, but retired, piece of essential daily routine. I was nervous to replace my pans sight unseen, but I would order two more without hesitation. I did give it a less than perfect score for sturdiness, because it doesn't handle being off balanced very well. For instance, chopped sweet potatoes on one side and halved brussel sprouts on the other, do not do well split down the middle. When the pan gets hot and it's not balanced, it will warp. It will also warp if it's too heavy and you don't properly support it out of the oven, haha. (that was definitely user error, but maybe not a issue on a sturdier pan) I rarely mix and match my veggies when baking, so it's rarely an issue for me. LOVE LOVE LOVE these pans!! Read more

top_reviews.title: Flimsier than expected
top_reviews.body: I got these pans to replace a pan that I wrecked by putting it on the grill. The new pans are a little flimsier than my 15-year-old pans that have stood the test of time. I am sure it will be fine, it’s still a Calphalon.  Update: Definitely not as sturdy as my 15 yo pans. The old ones weigh 3.25# and the new ones 1.9# They warp/twist in the oven on high heat. I will keep my eyes open for a heavier version. Read more

top_reviews.title: Very nice cookie sheets!
top_reviews.body: Heavy, sturdy cookie sheets. Nice non-stick surface. Great quality that I have come to expect from Caphalon. Arrived quickly. No issues at all. If I had one complaint it would be the rolled edge that leaves a gap for water to collect when washing. It's difficult to find cookie sheets that don't have a better design than this. Inevitably it will rust in this area and rusty water will run out during washing. Other than that I am very happy with my purchase. Read more
